This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it describes the design and testing of a neuromorphic network. The use of embedded nonvolatile floating-gate cell arrays also suggests that it could belong to the Emerging Technologies (cs.ET) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the peripheral circuitry for weight adjustment and I/O operations, which could place it in the Architecture (cs.AR) sub-category. The use of analog components and memory technology could also suggest that it belongs to the Electronic Materials (cs.EM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the energy efficiency of the circuit, which could place it in the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
